1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:02,167
<i> Mike is like a brother to me.</i>

2
00:00:02,167 --> 00:00:04,167
<i> What he wants, I want too.</i>

3
00:00:04,167 --> 00:00:05,667
<i> That's important in business.</i>

4
00:00:05,667 --> 00:00:07,233
<i>I trusted you
more than a friend!</i>

5
00:00:07,233 --> 00:00:08,500
[SCREAMS]

6
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:09,500
[HITS]

7
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:11,600
[SCREAMS]

8
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,967
<i> I know you know something.</i>

9
00:00:12,967 --> 00:00:14,000
<i> Just say it!</i>

10
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,733
<i> Even if we kill each other...</i>

11
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:17,133
<i>you still won't get
anything from me!</i>

12
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,000
- [GRUNTS]
- [KICK LANDS]

13
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,033
- [SCREAMS]
- [THUDS]

14
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:22,600
- [LEAVES RUSTLE]
- We're safe now,

15
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,067
<i> our whole family is safe.</i>

16
00:00:24,067 --> 00:00:25,533
<i>We don't have
any rivals anymore</i>

17
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:27,767
<i>for the hidden treasure
in this hotel.</i>

18
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:30,167
<i>You said you have something
important to tell us.</i>

19
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:32,600
<i>Later, when your
two siblings arrive.</i>

20
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,500
- [PHONE CHIMES]
- Your father sent a message.

21
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,800
<i>He's asking you
to come to the hotel.</i>

22
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:36,933
<i>He's not a good father,
Mommyla.</i>

23
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:38,000
<i> We both know that.</i>

24
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,633
<i>We'll be having a get-together
at Hotel 88.</i>

25
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:41,633
<i> It feels just like before.</i>

26
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:42,900
<i>The last time
we went to the hotel</i>

27
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,133
<i> was more than ten years ago?</i>

28
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:45,633
<i> And now everything's okay?</i>

29
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,867
<i>What matters is that
they're getting along now.</i>

30
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:52,633
[THWACK]

31
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:57,000
I'm surprised you came.

32
00:00:58,133 --> 00:01:00,067
You haven't come home
for years.

33
00:01:00,067 --> 00:01:01,800
And now you're finally
visiting your father?

34
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,033
I just want to find out
what's going on.

35
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:05,867
Aren't you curious?

36
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:09,167
Papa and Uncle Fred
suddenly made up.

37
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:15,700
I don't ask Papa about him
and Uncle Mike, but...

38
00:01:16,667 --> 00:01:17,633
[THWACK]

39
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,767
You know...

40
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:21,267
Peace is good, right?

41
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:24,300
- Yes.
- [SIGHS]

42
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:31,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:38,300
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:02:31,233 --> 00:02:32,900
Alright, I'll leave you here
for now.

45
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:35,233
I'm going to the market
and picking someone up.

46
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:37,700
There are restaurants
around here, but...

47
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:38,667
since you might be
saving money,

48
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:41,100
just do some
window shopping first, okay?

49
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,167
Bye-bye!

50
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:43,800
- Take care! [CLEARS THROAT]
- Bye! Take care!

51
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:51,733
Miss, how much is one bibingka?

52
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:54,700
Uhm, it's 3 for 100 pesos,
or 35 pesos each.

53
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:57,233
- The 35 pesos.
- Okay.

54
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,867
- Here, sir.
- Here's my payment.

55
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:06,200
Hmm!

56
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,667
[JADE] Paint whatever
makes you happy.

57
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,300
Okay?

58
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:20,200
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

59
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:41,833
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
CONTINUES]

60
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,100
[CHOKES]

61
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:49,833
[COUGHS]

62
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:53,067
[COUGHING, CHOKING]

63
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,967
[KIKO COUGHING]

64
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:56,833
Oh my god!

65
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,767
Oh my god! Oh my god!
Oh my god!

66
00:03:58,767 --> 00:03:59,767
Sir?

67
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:01,167
Sir! Sir-- [SQUEALS]

68
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:02,500
- [COUGHING]
- Sir, I'll help you!

69
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:04,233
- I'll help you, spit it out!
- [COUGHING]

70
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:05,433
- Spit it out, sir!
- [COUGHING]

71
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:06,433
Spit it out! [GRUNTS]

72
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:10,033
[COUGHING]

73
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:11,433
- Sir, are you o-okay?
- [COUGHING]

74
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:13,100
Do you need to go
to the hospital?

75
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:14,900
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

76
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:17,900
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
CONTINUES]

77
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:18,900
Jade?!

78
00:04:21,233 --> 00:04:22,467
You know me?

79
00:04:22,467 --> 00:04:23,867
Yes! It's me, Kiko!

80
00:04:24,767 --> 00:04:26,933
- Kiko?
- Kiko from Hotel 88.

81
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:30,467
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
CONTINUES]

82
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,367
- [CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY] Ah...
- How are you?

83
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:34,233
I'm okay.

84
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:37,867
Actually, um...
I'm kind of in a hurry.

85
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:40,633
Bye.

86
00:04:40,633 --> 00:04:46,167
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
CONTINUES]

87
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:47,233
You're in charge here, okay?

88
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:54,800
[RAPHIE] Sir Gio!

89
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,100
Uh, h-hello.

90
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:05,167
- Are you hotel staff?
- Uh, yes.

91
00:05:05,167 --> 00:05:06,333
I'm Raphie, sir.

92
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:09,933
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:11,900
- Raprap?
- Uh...

94
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:13,967
Raprap in the past,

95
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:15,300
Raphie in the present.

96
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,467
Very present!

97
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:17,567
I have two bags,

98
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,933
make sure nothing
gets left behind.

99
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:20,033
Okay, sir.

100
00:05:22,233 --> 00:05:23,467
Where's the service?

101
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:26,300
We're all riding together
with Miss Monette and Sir Kiko

102
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:28,033
back to Isla Solara, sir.

103
00:05:28,033 --> 00:05:29,967
Isn't there a welcome drink?
It's hot.

104
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:33,467
Uh, we're not at the
actual hotel yet, sir, but...

105
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:34,400
over there!

106
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,000
We can get some there.

107
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,467
Shall we get some drinks?

108
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:39,867
- Is it far?
- Oh, the basket.

109
00:05:39,867 --> 00:05:46,367
[CHILL MUSIC PLAYING]

110
00:05:46,367 --> 00:05:48,500
- How far is it?
- It's just right there, sir.

111
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:00,233
Gio! [CHUCKLES SLIGHTLY]

112
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:03,933
Gio!

113
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,233
How are you?

114
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:08,333
Uh bro, I'm okay, okay.

115
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:11,867
[KIKO] Sorry.

116
00:06:12,533 --> 00:06:14,567
Sorry.

117
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:21,433
Martin is also coming here,
Raphie said.

118
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,300
He might already be there.

119
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:30,067
There! There he is!

120
00:06:30,567 --> 00:06:31,567
[CLEARS THROAT]

121
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,033
Martin!

122
00:06:34,567 --> 00:06:35,500
How are you?

123
00:06:36,933 --> 00:06:43,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:07:10,267 --> 00:07:11,400
[SIGHS]

125
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:13,933
My children!

126
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:19,600
Oh! We finally see
each other again.

127
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:22,400
- Pa.
- Oh!

128
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:23,933
[CHUCKLES]

129
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,333
He's drunk again.

130
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:26,633
Hmm!

131
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:37,133
Oh, Gio.

132
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,000
Tuna! Your favorite.

133
00:07:40,467 --> 00:07:42,067
Come on, eat!

134
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:45,400
- Go on, eat now!
- Come on.

135
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:48,633
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

136
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:50,300
- Sorry, excuse me.
- [CHAIR SLIDES]

137
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:51,667
I'm not really feeling well.

138
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:53,467
I'll be in my room
just in case.

139
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:56,200
Oh!

140
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:58,000
Come on, eat now!

141
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:01,033
- Let's celebrate!
- I'm still full.

142
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:06,267
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:08:06,267 --> 00:08:07,433
Pa.

144
00:08:07,433 --> 00:08:08,500
Wait a second.

145
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,300
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

146
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,367
Why did I even come?
[SIGHS]

147
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:26,833
Same question.

148
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,733
After all these years,

149
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:31,933
Papa hasn't changed a bit.

150
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:35,100
He still greets us drunk.

151
00:08:36,367 --> 00:08:39,100
I'm just here because there's
something important to discuss.

152
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:41,267
It's probably
about money, right?

153
00:08:41,967 --> 00:08:42,967
[EXHALES]

154
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,200
Let's go back.

155
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:47,233
I shouldn't have come.

156
00:08:47,867 --> 00:08:49,167
Yeah, maybe.

157
00:08:49,367 --> 00:08:50,567
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:53,767
But whatever the reason
you're here today...

159
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,733
You, Martin,

160
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:59,767
and you too, Gio,

161
00:09:00,467 --> 00:09:02,233
you're both already here.

162
00:09:02,933 --> 00:09:05,833
So let's go back,
please, and be with Papa.

163
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:07,867
[SIGHS]

164
00:09:10,067 --> 00:09:16,933
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:23,333
[SIGHS]

166
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,333
[BOTTLE THUDS]

167
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,400
[MUSIC FADES]

168
00:09:33,933 --> 00:09:35,167
[SIGHS]

169
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:37,100
Why did I expect something
different was going to happen?

170
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,000
Can you believe it,
after all this time,

171
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,167
they ended up falling out?

172
00:09:41,167 --> 00:09:44,267
You know, those brothers
used to be so close and happy.

173
00:09:44,467 --> 00:09:47,267
They got along even though
they had different mothers.

174
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:49,267
And they even had
their childhood friends,

175
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,800
the Almazans, right?

176
00:09:51,133 --> 00:09:52,900
It's only the first day.

177
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,933
Doesn't they say
the world is healing?

178
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:57,067
Maybe it's just normal
to be like that at first.

179
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:59,067
Healing, my foot.
Get moving.

180
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:00,000
They'll be here any minute.

181
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,733
- We have to get changed.
- Oh, right.

182
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,200
It's so early in the morning.

183
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:10,367
Come on, Gio.
Please help me.

184
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:12,333
- Just get this.
- [GIO] Look how dirty that is.

185
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:13,400
Come on.

186
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:15,033
Thank you.

187
00:10:16,467 --> 00:10:17,867
[KIKO] This one, too.

188
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:20,367
Kiko, all this stuff
is covered in dust.

189
00:10:20,367 --> 00:10:23,300
Come on, please.
I swear, it's just these.

190
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,467
What are you doing?

191
00:10:24,467 --> 00:10:27,233
- I have no idea with this guy.
- [KIKO] There it is!

192
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:30,367
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:31,800
Whoa, it's heavy.

194
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:33,433
[STRAINING] Oops.

195
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:37,867
- This one's yours, right?
- Is that mine?

196
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:39,400
Yeah, look.

197
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,233
And this is Gio's.

198
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,333
Does it still work?
Let me see.

199
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:47,300
- Is it going to work?
- I don't know.

200
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:48,533
This is silly.

201
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:51,267
I kept them there.

202
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,067
[MUSIC FADES]

203
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,367
I always check on them.

204
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,467
I told myself,

205
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,267
when Martin and Gio come visit,

206
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,800
they'll have bikes
they can use.

207
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:08,033
But what if Kiko...

208
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:11,400
Anyway, you've grown up now.

209
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,233
You won't be able to use
those bikes anymore.

210
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:18,000
They're worn down.

211
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,833
You stopped coming home.

212
00:11:26,267 --> 00:11:28,033
You stopped visiting.

213
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:32,000
Why is that?

214
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:38,100
It's just...
we've been busy, Pa.

215
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,567
Do you really want
to know why, Pa?

216
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,867
Martin.

217
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:44,967
He needs to know the truth.

218
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:50,033
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS]

219
00:11:51,267 --> 00:11:52,533
It's you.

220
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:56,267
You're toxic.

221
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,067
Your drinking,

222
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:02,200
your being an
irresponsible father...

223
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:08,300
There are so many reasons
we stopped coming home.

224
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:13,300
What are the reasons you don't
come home anymore?

225
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,600
Tell me.

226
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:19,967
I'll listen. I have time.
What have I done?

227
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,667
[CLATTERS]

228
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:24,167
[GIO] Stop it.

229
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:26,467
Pa, is this what you want?

230
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,367
Is this why you
asked us to come?

231
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,633
That's what you want?
A blame game?

232
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:36,333
This is wasting my time.
I'm leaving.

233
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:38,367
Hold on.

234
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,467
I know I've done a lot
to hurt you.

235
00:12:43,067 --> 00:12:45,400
I've failed you
in so many ways.

236
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:48,600
But that's why
I asked you here.

237
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:51,067
So we can make things right.

238
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:56,100
So we can talk about
these shortcomings.

239
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,967
Let's rebuild our family.

240
00:13:01,733 --> 00:13:03,433
Even this hotel.

241
00:13:03,967 --> 00:13:05,467
Let's bring it back
to how it used to be.

242
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,367
Let's start over.

243
00:13:09,367 --> 00:13:12,567
I want us to run
this hotel together.

244
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:21,533
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:44,567
[SIGHS]

246
00:13:56,600 --> 00:14:03,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,133
[BOTTLE THUDS]

248
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:13,433
[MUSIC BECOMES CURIOUS]

249
00:14:29,733 --> 00:14:36,633
[CURIOUS MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

250
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:51,767
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

251
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:07,167
[MUSIC BECOMES UNSETTLING]

252
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:15,267
[KEYS JINGLE]

253
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:19,567
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

254
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:27,200
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:32,633
[TIRES SCRAPE]

256
00:15:33,367 --> 00:15:40,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

257
00:15:46,633 --> 00:15:48,600
- [ENGINE REVS]
- [TIRES SCREECH]

258
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,400
[TIRES SCREECH]

259
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,300
[ENGINE REVS]

260
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:57,233
Ma?

261
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,800
Let's go?

262
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,500
Um... [STAMMERS]
Alright.

263
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,333
Alright, go ahead.
Bring your siblings.

264
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,000
Your father and I will follow.

265
00:16:05,433 --> 00:16:06,767
I think he went out.

266
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:08,600
Oh? Okay.

267
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,900
See you.

268
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:15,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:18,300
Hello. What's up?

270
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,667
Kiko, let me do that!

271
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:21,833
- I'll be here a little longer.
- It's okay, Monette.

272
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:22,933
They'll be here any minute.

273
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,700
Fine, I'll make it up to you.

274
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,467
When I get home,
let's play golf.

275
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:29,300
Who were you with
last time?

276
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,900
- Monette?
- Yeah?

277
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,600
Isn't Papa coming out yet?

278
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:35,033
Oh, he left in a rush earlier.

279
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:36,900
He seemed upset.

280
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:40,600
But he'll come back.
He won't be gone for too long.

281
00:16:40,867 --> 00:16:45,333
You should sort things out
with your brothers.

282
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,800
You seem to be living
in different worlds.

283
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,833
- [MARTIN] Okay.
- The Almazans are here.

284
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,600
[MARTIN]
Take care. I have to go.

285
00:16:54,933 --> 00:16:55,967
[LEON] What's up?

286
00:16:56,433 --> 00:17:03,300
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:12,667
[MUSIC BECOMES UNEASY]

288
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:27,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES, FADES]

289
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:30,533
[MIKE] How do you expect me
to believe a liar like you?

290
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:34,500
Our agreement
was crystal clear.

291
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:35,700
We agreed that...

292
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,067
[INAUDIBLE]

293
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:39,967
[INDISTINCT ARGUMENT]

294
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:43,900
I didn't betray
this friendship.

295
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:45,667
- You did!
- Me?!

296
00:17:46,867 --> 00:17:47,967
[TENSE MUSIC STING]

297
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:51,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

298
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,033
Point the gun at me!

299
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:56,000
[MUSIC FADES]

300
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:58,033
[LUNA]
Mama told us to go ahead.

301
00:17:58,033 --> 00:17:59,600
[RAPHIE]
Sir Gio, drinks?

302
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:01,433
- [MONETTE] Here's the food.
- [KIKO] Let me get that.

303
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:02,600
Oh, okay.

304
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:07,767
Where's Uncle Michael?

305
00:18:08,567 --> 00:18:11,533
Uh, he'll probably
be here soon.

306
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,033
I haven't heard from him.

307
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:15,567
[MARTIN] I don't know.

308
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:17,700
- [RAPHIE] Sir...
- [MARTIN] He'll be here.

309
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:20,000
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

310
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,533
[MARTIN] It's been so long
since we last got together.

311
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:24,800
- [LUNA] Ten years, actually.
- [MARTIN] Ten years?

312
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:26,800
Nothing's changed.

313
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:30,833
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

314
00:18:31,433 --> 00:18:32,600
Um...

315
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:35,800
Have you been teaching painting
to kids for a long time?

316
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:37,600
[CLEARS THROAT]

317
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:38,967
Uh...

318
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,600
Yes.

319
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,967
It's an outreach program
Daddy and I created.

320
00:18:43,533 --> 00:18:44,600
Oh.

321
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:47,467
Do you want this?

322
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:52,567
No, it's okay. I'm full.
Thanks.

323
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:55,700
- [GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BIRDS CHIRP]

324
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:58,567
[LEON] We haven't seen
each other in ten years.

325
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:00,033
That's long.

326
00:19:00,033 --> 00:19:02,067
[MARTIN]
But we still look the same.

327
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:04,067
We haven't changed a bit.

328
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:05,967
- Juice?
- We were so young.

329
00:19:06,233 --> 00:19:07,533
All of us were so little.

330
00:19:07,533 --> 00:19:08,800
No, I'm good. Thank you.

331
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,233
- It would be a waste.
- I'm not thirsty.

332
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:13,733
- [LEON]...every Easter.
- It tastes good.

333
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:19,633
But it's nice to see
the three of you again.

334
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:21,433
Feels like...

335
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:23,033
the old days.

336
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,867
All of us together...

337
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,567
here at the hotel.

338
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,100
[MUSIC FADES]

339
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,200
Aren't you going to
call your father?

340
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,733
I'm starving.

341
00:19:36,533 --> 00:19:39,167
Uh, I'll check.
He might be here already.

342
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:40,967
Wait a minute.

343
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,667
[DARK MUSIC PLAYS]

344
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:46,467
- Uh...
- [OFFICER] Sir's gone, ma'am.

345
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:48,133
What?

346
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:50,833
[GASPS]

347
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:53,700
What happened?!

348
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:54,967
[TENSE MUSIC STING]

349
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:56,133
[MONETTE WAILS]

350
00:19:56,633 --> 00:19:57,833
No!

351
00:19:58,033 --> 00:20:01,733
[MONETTE CRIES]

352
00:20:02,533 --> 00:20:08,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

353
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,667
- [SIREN WAILING
- [FRIDA] No! No! No!

354
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:13,233
Sir, sir!
You're not allowed here!

355
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:14,467
- [FRIDA] No!
- Stop right there, ma'am!

356
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:16,133
Ma'am! Stop right there.

357
00:20:16,133 --> 00:20:21,000
- [CRYING]
- [SIREN WAILING]

358
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,067
No!

359
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:24,067
- [CRYING]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

360
00:20:24,067 --> 00:20:25,167
Fred!

361
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:27,200
[CRYING]

362
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:34,000
- [SIREN WAILING]
- [CRYING, WAILING]

363
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:37,367
[SCREAMING, WAILING]

364
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,567
- [CRYING]
- [FRIDA] No! No!

365
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:43,633
[FRIDA BREATHES HEAVILY]
Fred...

366
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:47,233
[CRYING]

367
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,367
- Wait!
- Papa!

368
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:51,467
[WAILING] Papa!

369
00:20:51,467 --> 00:20:55,067
- Papa--
- [BAWLING, CRYING]

370
00:20:55,067 --> 00:20:57,533
Pa! [WAILING]

371
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:05,400
- [CRYING, BAWLING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

372
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:11,333
[BAWLING]

373
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:13,000
Papa! [WAILS]

374
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:19,733
- [SKY RUMBLING]
- [CRYING, BAWLING]

375
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,700
We're asking politely,

376
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:23,667
all the family members need
to step aside first.

377
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:28,033
- [KIKO] No!
- Sorry.

378
00:21:28,033 --> 00:21:29,367
Please, go ahead.
I'm sorry.

379
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:31,100
[CRIES, SOBS]

380
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,400
- [SKY RUMBLING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

381
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:36,133
[BAWLING] Pa!

382
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:38,733
[SOBS]
Why did you leave us?!

383
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:44,467
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

384
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:49,100
- [CRYING, SOBBING]
- [SKY RUMBLING]

385
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:53,700
[CRYING, WHIMPERING]

386
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:55,067
I don't want to!

387
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:57,100
I don't want to,
I don't want to!

388
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:58,333
Papa!

389
00:21:58,333 --> 00:21:59,767
Mrs. Almazan, we're sorry.

390
00:21:59,767 --> 00:22:01,733
We have to do our work first.

391
00:22:01,733 --> 00:22:03,333
- [SOBS]
- Please.

392
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:05,400
[OFFICER] Sorry.
It's just our work.

393
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:08,400
- [RAIN POURING]
- [CRYING]

394
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:12,567
- [SKY RUMBLING, RAIN POURING]
- [BAWLING]

395
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:15,400
Daddy! No! No!

396
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:16,700
Dad!

397
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:18,267
Please.

398
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:20,633
Sorry, it's just work.
You're not allowed here.

399
00:22:20,633 --> 00:22:22,167
Sir, sir!

400
00:22:22,167 --> 00:22:24,633
- Miss, please!
- [SCREAMS]

401
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:27,267
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WAILING]

402
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:28,433
Sir, please.

403
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:30,367
[CRYING]

404
00:22:32,533 --> 00:22:36,200
[CRYING, SOBBING]

405
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:40,100
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

406
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:42,100
[SKY RUMBLING]

407
00:22:46,967 --> 00:22:53,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

408
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:57,800
[SNIFFLES]

409
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:01,633
It's supposed to be
your reconciliation dinner.

410
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:06,700
But this is what happened.

411
00:23:07,867 --> 00:23:09,833
Why were they together?

412
00:23:11,033 --> 00:23:12,833
They even got to meet earlier.

413
00:23:13,567 --> 00:23:15,167
And they didn't even tell you?

414
00:23:15,700 --> 00:23:17,933
Ma! Why?

415
00:23:17,933 --> 00:23:18,933
[INHALES SHARPLY]

416
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:20,800
I don't know.

417
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:24,800
[SOBS]

418
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:27,200
This shouldn't have
happened to Dad.

419
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:30,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

420
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,533
Right?

421
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,767
Mom?

422
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:37,733
[SNIFFLES]
That's why we'll do...

423
00:23:37,733 --> 00:23:40,467
we'll do everything...

424
00:23:40,667 --> 00:23:42,633
for the truth.

425
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:45,467
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- [MUSIC TURNS DRAMATIC]

426
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:47,433
We won't stop...

427
00:23:47,733 --> 00:23:50,600
until someone has paid
for what happened to Dad.

428
00:23:53,700 --> 00:24:00,700
- [SOBBING] Brother.
- It's okay. I'm right here.

429
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:07,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

430
00:24:07,233 --> 00:24:09,800
[WHIMPERS]

431
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:13,633
[SOBBING]

432
00:24:15,067 --> 00:24:16,733
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

433
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:19,500
<i>The investigation has also
become faster because</i>

434
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,733
<i>of the strong testimony
from the witness.</i>

435
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:24,033
<i>So what?
Can't you show some concern?</i>

436
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:26,033
<i> No! That's not true!</i>

437
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:28,033
<i> That was self-defense!</i>

438
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:30,800
<i>There's no reason for me to
stay here anymore without him!</i>

439
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:34,000
<i>We'll do everything
for the truth.</i>

440
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:38,000
We won't stop until someone has
paid for what happened to Dad.

441
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

